# Trivy ignore file — suppressions for findings that are accepted by design.
#
# DS-0002: "Image user should not be 'root'".
# This is a VPN gateway container: its s6-overlay init (PID 1) must run as root
# to manage iptables firewall rules (rebuilt on every reconnect), create/tear
# down the wg0 device, and edit routing tables (NET_ADMIN). WireGuard runs
# in-kernel, so there is no long-running userspace daemon that could drop
# privileges. A USER directive would break container init, so there is no fix
# that satisfies this rule without breaking the image.
AVD-DS-0002
DS-0002
